snippet: Wilson Ramos hit a two-run homer in the seventh inning, and the Nationals won a ninth straight game started by Jordan Zimmermann.
abstract: Baseball Roundup; Washington Nationals beat New York Mets, 3-0, to eliminate them from postseason contention; other scores noted.
lead_paragraph: Wilson Ramos hit a two-run homer in the seventh inning, and the Nationals won a ninth straight game started by Jordan Zimmermann.

headline.main: Nationals Eliminate Mets From Division Race; Dodgers’ Clayton Kershaw Earns 19th Win
headline.print_headline: Nationals Eliminate Mets From Division Race; Dodgers’ Kershaw Wins 19th
